title: PPPP’s candidate Adil Altaf wins PS-13 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Adil Altaf Und has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-13 Larkana-IV constituency by securing 89,662 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Naseer Muhammad of of Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) who bagged 4,028 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.64 percent in the constituency.
